### GET COURSES
## Returns a list of courses filtered by semester. The result set is scoped
## to the authenticated user's role:
##   - Student -> only courses the student is enrolled in
##   - Teacher -> only courses the teacher is assigned to
##   - Local Admin -> all courses within the admin's school
##   - Admin -> all courses across all schools
##
## Request Body:
##   - semester_id (UUID, required): The UUID of the semester to filter courses by
##
## Response Body (200 OK) - Array of course objects, each containing:
##   - course_id              (UUID) : Unique identifier of the course
##   - course_name            (string): Full name of the course (e.g. "Wirtschaft und Recht")
##   - course_abbreviation    (string): Short identifier (e.g. "WR")
##   - course_description     (string): Description of the course
##   - teacher_first_name     (string): First name of the assigned teacher
##   - teacher_last_name      (string): Last name of the assigned teacher
##   - teacher_email          (string): Email of the assigned teacher
##   - teacher_phone          (string): Phone number of the assigned teacher
##   - teacher_address        (string): Address of the assigned teacher
##   - class_name             (string): Name of the class this course belongs to
##
## Responses:
##   200 OK - Returns array of GetCourseResponse objects
##   400 Bad Request -  Missing or invalid semester_id
##   403 Forbidden - No active session
##   500 Internal Server Error - Database Query failed
GET {{BASE}}/course
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
    "semester_id": "a8a31a4d-abce-48d2-82f0-555f15e27694"
}


### CREATE A COURSE
## Creates a new course and associates it with a teacher, class, and semester.
## Restricted to Local Admin or Admin roles.
##
## Request Body:
##   - name         (string, required): Full course name (e.g. "Wirtschaft und Recht")
##   - abbreviation (string, required): Short course identifier (e.g. "WR")
##   - description  (string, required): Human-readable description of the course
##   - teacher      (UUID, required): UUID of the teacher assigned to this course
##   - class        (UUID, required): UUID of the class this course is assigned to
##   - semester     (UUID, required): UUID of the semester this course runs in
##   - school_id    (UUID, optional): UUID of the school; only necessary if a admin creates a course
##
## Responses:
##   201 Created - Course created successfully; returns the new course ID
##   400 Bad Request - Missing required fields or invalid UUID format
##   401 Unauthorized - Insufficient permissions for this role
##   403 Forbidden - No active session
##   404 Not Found - Teacher, class, semester, or school UUID does not exist
##   500 Internal Server Error - Database Query failed
##
# @name wr
POST {{BASE}}/course
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json


{
    "name": "Wirtschaft und Recht",
    "abbreviation": "WR",
    "description": "Wirtschaft und recht für die Klasse 3e",
    "teacher": "df316fca-23d0-4f2f-9f16-545dd2372956",
    "class": "00d92156-6f0f-491d-a224-15e2155627f1",
    "semester": "a8a31a4d-abce-48d2-82f0-555f15e27694",
    "school_id": "2c64f5d3-4c82-4474-acf6-caa82be28f66"
}


### EDIT A COURSE
## Partially updates an existing course identified by its UUID in the path.
## Only the fields provided in the request body will be updated (PATCH semantics).
## Restricted to Local Admin or Admin roles.
##
## Path Parameter:
##   - {course_id} (UUID): The UUID of the course to update
##
## Request Body (all fields optional - only included fields are updated):
##   - name         (string, optional): New full course name
##   - abbreviation (string, optional): New short course identifier
##   - description  (string, optional): New description text
##   - teacher      (UUID, optional): UUID of the newly assigned teacher
##   - class        (UUID, optional): UUID of the newly assigned class
##
## Responses:
##   200 OK - Course updated successfully; returns updated course object
##   400 Bad Request - Invalid UUID format or malformed body
##   401 Unauthorized - Insufficient permissions for this role
##   403 Forbidden - No active session
##   404 Not Found - Course, teacher, or class UUID does not exist
##   500 Internal Server Error - Database Query failed
PATCH {{BASE}}/course/{{wr.response.body.resource_id}}
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
    "description": "Wirtschaft und recht für die Klasse 4e"
}


### DELETE A COURSE
## Permanently deletes a course identified by its UUID in the path.
## This action is irreversible. 
## Restricted to Local Admin or Admin roles.
##
## Path Parameter:
##   - {course_id} (UUID): The UUID of the course to delete
##
## Responses:
##   200 OK - Course deleted successfully
##   401 Unauthorized - Insufficient permissions for this role
##   403 Forbidden - No active session
##   404 Not Found - Course UUID does not exist
DELETE {{BASE}}/course/{{wr.response.body.resource_id}}
Accept: application/json
